    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-04-23T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-04-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="560"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/749a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-04-23T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1927—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>182. Your 24, January 12, 10 a.m. For your information. Radio Corporation informs
                    Department that as result of American communications of October last to Japanese
                    and Chinese Government[s] it had felt encouraged to continue support of Federal
                    Telegraph Company of Delaware, but that it now feels that it cannot continue
                    such support much longer. Department is requesting Japanese Embassy to reply to
                    memorandum of October 28 last.<note n="37" xml:id="d560fn37">
                        <ref target="frus1926v01#pg_1082">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 1082</ref>.</note> Please report
                    present situation and prospects for any future action by Peking authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
